  "description": "The engine's home terrain made explicit: the Mesopelagic Zone, 200-1000m depth, twilight diffusion. E constant at depth 5 — convergents have tightened toward e/2 but not yet clumped — produces a narrow spectral band, three or four partials audibly distinct. Partial amplitudes weighted toward the middle (1, 2, 3 boosted; 0 and 7 reduced) so the sound occupies a choir-like mid-register rather than a sub drone. Attack 1.8s — the water column takes time to pressurize. Very slow LFOs at 0.03 Hz give each note a barely-audible swell. Filter at 5500 Hz filters out the upper mathematicality, leaving only the pressure. Resonator at 0.65 adds the cave-choir resonance of deep water.",
